other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated to 10 mm with mild surrounding inflammatory changes and surrounding fat stranding, particularly at the tip. No drainable fluid collection or extraluminal gas is seen. The visualized lung bases demonstrate mild bibasilar atelectasis. The visualized heart is normal in size without pericardial effusion. Two subcentimeter hypodensities are visualized in the liver, which are too small to characterize.
